      "text": "%md\n**Note on SQL:** Here we use **spark.sql(\"...\").show()** — the same API as in **Google Colab** (in Colab you use the same calls without the %livy2.pyspark line). In Zeppelin you can also use a **%livy2.sql** (or **%sql**) paragraph and write raw SQL; that is similar to **%%sql** in HDInsight. Both run the same SQL against the same Spark session.",
