            "data": "<p><strong>Note on SQL:</strong> Here we use <strong>spark.sql(\"...\").show()</strong> — the same API as in <strong>Google Colab</strong> (in Colab you use the same calls without the %livy2.pyspark line). In Zeppelin you can also use a <strong>%livy2.sql</strong> (or <strong>%sql</strong>) paragraph and write raw SQL; that is similar to <strong>%%sql</strong> in HDInsight. Both run the same SQL against the same Spark session.</p>"
